\h STOP \d

\uUSAGE\n
stop \s[\daction\s]\d

\uDESCRIPTION\n
Stop moving, eating, drinking, or attacking.

This command may take the following forms:
\qstop moving\d    (or just \qstop m\d) to stop moving.4`
\qstop eating\d    (or just \qstop e\d) to stop eating.4`
\qstop drinking\d  (or just \qstop d\d) to stop drinking.4`
\qstop attacking\d (or just \qstop a\d) to stop attacking.4`
\qstop\d with no arguments.4`

When no arguments are provided, you will stop carrying out a single action; the action you stop depends on what you are doing at the time. Namely, if currently moving, you will stop moving; otherwise if currently eating, you will stop eating, and so on (followed with drinking and attacking).

